{
  "stem": "26983.11",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Later on, on the way, it was again of luck, I remember, near Katowice, suddenly there was some possibly English airplanes, bombed a train of German soldiers who were next to us.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some of the soldiers went under our trains because they hoped this way they would be safe.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But by machine guns they killed them, and of course many of us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Again, what meant luck-- in these wagons there was a tiny little window and everyone tried to be near this window to have a bit of fresh air, and we took turns.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember just I had my turn, but I gave it to somebody else, to a friend of mine, and exactly where he stood, he was shot to death.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A bullet.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And somebody else from our group was also wounded or killed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Anyhow, in the next station they took the dead people out and just throw them out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know what happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We passed again, because it was a very well known railway connection in the station, [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, which now was the second time, or third time I passed it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I went to Theresienstadt, from Theresienstadt to Auschwitz, and now from Auschwitz to-- on the way to I didn't know where.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But anyhow, we stopped there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the early morning.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People, workers, went to work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they saw us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were on a little bridge like on the railway station, and they had their lunch and they throw it to us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And especially I could somehow to communicate with them, because they couldn't guard the whole train.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I spoke the language and therefore, into our wagon they brought us a bit of coffee.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Their own--",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
